Fix: reject empty task titles with 400 invalid_task (issue i1)

The bug: POST /tasks with title="" (or null/missing) returned 201.
Root cause: create_task passed the raw title straight to the store without
validating it.

The fix (service.py, create_task):

-def create_task(owner, title):
-    row = store.insert(owner=owner, title=title)
-    return _row_to_task(row)
+def create_task(owner, title):
+    clean = _validate_title(title)          # raises ValidationError if empty
+    row = store.insert(owner=owner, title=clean)
+    return _row_to_task(row)

_validate_title (already defined at service.py:37) raises ValidationError for
None, "", and whitespace-only strings. handle_create_task in api.py already
catches ValidationError and returns 400 invalid_task.

Current working-copy state: the fix IS in place at service.py:50. No file
edits needed; the change just needs to be committed.
